column2: 1991        MB-BcH    Mansoura university _ Egypt.
1996        M.S.           Master in surgery Kasr Elini School of medicine of Cairo University.
2000        Observer-ship at William Beaumont hospital (USA  -  Texas).
2003        A.L.S.        Provider at European resuscitation & intensive care council.
2010        MD           of cardiothoracic surgery – Mansoura University – Egypt.
2013         Approved as Consultant
1992    H.O.         Mansoura University Hospitals in medicine & surgery – Egypt.
1993    S.H.O.      in orthopedic, general surgery (Armed Forces Maadi Hospital) Egypt.
1994    S.H.O.      in cardiothoracic surgery (Armed Forces Maadi hospital) Egypt.
1996    S.H.O.      in casualty & emergency  surgery( Kasr Elini school of medicine) Egypt.
1997    registrar, cardiothoracic surgery (Armed Forces Maadi hospital) Egypt.
2000     visiting clinical observer    at William Beaumont Army Medical Centre –El-paso-Texas-USA .
2002    Senior registrar     cardiothoracic surgery (Armed Forces Maadi Hospital) Egypt.
2006    visiting registrar   cardiothoracic surgery dep., Mansoura  University, Egypt.
2010    junior consultant, cardiothoracic surgery (Armed Forces Maadi hospital) Egypt.
2010 – 2013 (4 years) Responsible for congenital heart surgery program in Maadi A. F. Hospital.
2010 – 2013 (4 years)  main assistant for prof. KAMAL MANSOUR's visits in Maadi
2014   (since Feb. up till now) cardiothoracic consultant at Specialized AirForces Hospital SAFH
2014 JOINED to cardiothoracic department  at international medical center  as consultant.
2014 ( in November ) visiting clinical observer  for ECMO and C.A.Ds at  Hanover Medical School
